  > Genetics
    Gene variants that impact body fatness are primarily related to brain function — not primarily {Concepts.Insulin insulin} or {Concepts.Adipocyte fat cells} (although many mechanisms may contribute to a smaller degree). Obesity risk is strongly influenced by genetics, and studies have begun to uncover the specific genetic differences that make some people fatter than others.
