  > Appetite
    The brain regulates {Concepts.Appetite appetite}. Appetite is a motivational state that is generated by the brain– like all motivational states. A few review papers give a broad overview about the appetite-regulating brain circuits work that can turn appetite on and off at will by controlling specific types of neurons in animals.
