  >
    During weight loss, the effect of increased hunger, more cravings, reduced metabolic rate, and eventual weight regain is due to decline in fat regulating hormone {Concepts.Leptin Leptin}. People with obesity “defend” a higher level of fat mass is because their brains require a higher level of leptin to feel like they aren’t starving.
